    <body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1981-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1981-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                        <head>406. Telegram From the Embassy in Czechoslovakia to the Department of
                                State<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d406fn1">Source: Department
                                of State, Central Foreign Policy File, D810527–1058. Confidential;
                                Immediate. Sent for information to Bern, Brussels, London, Paris,
                                and Zurich. The text of the claims agreement was sent to London on
                                November 13 in telegram 302976. (Department of State, Central
                                Foreign Policy File, D810540–0471)</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">4584.</seg><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName> Prague</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1981-11-06">November 6, 1981,
                            1425Z</date></dateline></opener>
                        <!--<pb facs="d406-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d406-2"/>-->
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Czechoslovak Claims Agreement.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Claims agreement was initialed November 6 by Charge and Director Kral of
                                <gloss target="#t_MFA_1">MFA</gloss> legal office. Initialed English
                            and Czech texts will be pouched November 10 and should arrive Washington
                            November 13.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MJ_2"><hi rend="strong">Matlock</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body>
  </text>
</TEI>
